<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS, AND BUMPER - WorkStar&#8482; Series Starting March 2007 - REMOVE AND INSTALL
        PROCEDURES - GRILLE AND BUG SCREEN
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="Remove and Install" graphiccount="3">
        <title>GRILLE AND BUG SCREEN</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Grille and Bug Screen - Removal</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Unlatch and open the hood.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0901402" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901402.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 3. Grille</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. GRILLE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. SCREW</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. MOUNT BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. LOWER MOUNT BRACKET</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. MOUNT TAB</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove two screws attaching the grille to the mount brackets on the radiator frame.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift grille upward to release the mount tabs from the lower mount bracket and remove the
                    grille.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the grille upside down on a padded surface to protect the finished surface of the
                    grille.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0901428" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901428.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4. Bug Screen</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. GRILLE</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. BUG SCREEN</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. RETAINER</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. MOUNT TAB</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove 16 retainers attaching the bug screen to the grille.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lift the bug screen off the grille.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If replacing grille, remove the mount tabs from the old grille and install them on the
                    new grille.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Grille and Bug Screen - Installation</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the bug screen on the grille and install the 16 retainers (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901428">Figure 4, Items 1, 2, and 3</hotlnk>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the mount tabs with the lower mount bracket and lower the grille into place (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901402">Figure 3, Items 4 and 5</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the holes and install two screws into the grille and mount brackets (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901402">Figure 3, Items 1, 2 and 3</hotlnk>). Torque screws to 6 to 7 lbf-ft (8 to
                    10 N&#8226;m).
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Grille Shroud - Removal</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The grille shroud should be removed with the hood in the closed position.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f0901403" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901403A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 5. Grille Shroud</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. GRILLE SHROUD</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. TAB INSERTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. HEADLIGHT ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove left side upper splash shield from hood.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove left and right side headlight assembly fasteners (4 nuts and 1 bolt per side) and
                    reposition headlight assemblies (see Figure 38 in Section 2.14 Headlight Assemblies).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the grille shroud by pulling the grille shroud out to release the tabs from the
                    tab inserts.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the grille shroud upside down on a padded surface to protect the finished surface
                    of the grille shroud.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Grille Shroud - Installation</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Prior to installing the grille shroud, inspect the mounting tabs on the inner surface of the
                        grille shroud. Insure that all tabs are functional and in place.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the grille shroud tabs with the tab inserts on the hood (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901403">Figure 5</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the grille shroud by carefully pushing the grille shroud tabs into the insert
                    tabs on the hood (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0901403">Figure 5</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install left and right side headlight assembly fasteners (4 nuts and 1 bolt per side).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install left side upper splash shield to hood.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
